<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#evidence876">
  <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Evidence"/>
  <evidenceContent rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Clear gifs are tiny graphics with a unique identifier, similar in function to cookies, and are used to track the online movements of Web users</evidenceContent>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#evidence877">
  <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Evidence"/>
  <evidenceContent rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">What are clear gifs? Clear gifs are tiny graphics with a unique identifier similar in function to cookies and are used to track the online movements of Web users In contrast to cookies which are stored on a users computer hard drive clear gifs are embedded invisibly on Web pages and are about the size of the full-stop or period at the end of this sentence</evidenceContent>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

