  <evidenceContent rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">13 NOTICE TO CALIFORNIA RESIDENTS CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS If you are a California resident and have provided us with Personally Identifiable Information California law gives you the right to request and receive from us once per calendar year information as to how we have shared your Personally Identifiable Information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes If applicable such information would include a list of names and addresses of all third parties with whom such information was shared during the prior calendar year as well as a list of the categories of Personally Identifiable Information shared To make such a request please send an email to businessaffairs lynda com and include the phrase California Privacy Request in the subject line Your request must also include your name physical mailing address and email address We will respond to you within thirty days of receiving such a request</evidenceContent>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

